The peak systolic velocity (PSV) is assessed as follows: >25 cm/s is considered to be normal, 20-25 cm/s is considered to be mild ED, 12-20 cm/s is considered to be moderate ED, <12 cm/s is considered to be severe arteriogenic impotence.
